Former Prime Minister Raila Odinga and former Cabinet Minister Simeon Nyachae at a past function. (Photo: Eric Abuga/Standard) CORD leader Raila Odinga Sunday condoled with former Cabinet Minister Simeon Nyachae over the demise of his wife Esther Nyachae. The former premier arrived at Nyachae&rsquo;s home in Nyosia village in Nyaribari Chache, Kisii County Sunday afternoon and was received by Governor James Ongwae. The late Esther will be buried today (Sept 5) at Nyosia, with President Uhuru Kenyatta and former President Daniel arap Moi expected to attend the burial.